
Overview of verb excoriate

The verb excoriate has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) condemn, reprobate, decry, objurgate, excoriate -- (express strong disapproval of; "We condemn the racism in South Africa"; "These ideas were reprobated")
2. chafe, excoriate -- (tear or wear off the skin or make sore by abrading; "This leash chafes the dog's neck")
